# Frontend standards

## Architecture

- **Components first**: repeated UI → component; repeated content → data (arrays, config files) + map.
- **One responsibility per file** where reasonable; avoid 800-line pages — compose sections.
- **Colocate**: `components/`, `data/`, `lib/` — predictable imports; use path aliases consistently (`@/`).

## Styling (Tailwind)

- **Utility-first, not utility-only soup**: extract patterns (cards, section shells) into components or `@apply` sparingly in CSS layers when it improves clarity.
- **Semantic tokens**: colors/spacing via design tokens (CSS variables + theme), not random hex in class strings scattered everywhere.
- **Responsive**: mobile-first breakpoints; verify touch targets and typography at `sm` / `md` / `lg`.

## HTML & accessibility

- **Semantic structure**: `header`, `main`, `nav`, `footer`, `section`, headings in order, `button` vs `a` correctly.
- **Accessible interactions**: visible focus rings, `aria-label` on icon-only controls, dialog `role`/`aria-modal`, form labels tied to inputs.
- **Images**: meaningful `alt`; decorative images `alt=""`; `sizes` for responsive `next/image`.

## Motion

- **Performant**: prefer `transform`/`opacity`; avoid animating `width`/`height`/layout thrash.
- **Framer Motion** (or similar): scope client components; don’t wrap the entire app in `"use client"` unnecessarily.

## Quality

- **DRY sensibly**: abstract the third duplication, not the first.
- **Types**: TypeScript for props and data shapes; avoid `any` for public components.
- **Lint/format**: respect project ESLint/Prettier; fix new violations you introduce.

## Forms & data

- **Structured steps** for multi-step flows; clear validation messages; loading/disabled states on submit.
